---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Plot Loan - Buy Residential or Commercial Land | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Plot Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Plot Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Purchase residential or commercial plots with a dedicated plot loan at interest rates starting from 8.75% p.a. Get up to 70% financing on the plot value with tenures up to 15 years. Build your dream home on your own land.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹5L - ₹1 Cr</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-days"></i>
          <span>Tenure: 1-15 Years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 8.75% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Plot Loan?</h2>
          <p>A plot loan (also called a land purchase loan) is a secured loan specifically designed to finance the purchase of a residential or commercial plot of land. Unlike home loans used to buy constructed properties, plot loans fund the land acquisition only. Once you purchase the plot, you can subsequently avail a home construction loan to build your house. Plot loans typically cover up to 70% of the plot value and come with slightly higher interest rates than regular home loans.</p>
          <p>At TrueCred Loan Expert, we help you find the best plot loan offers from over 25 banks and housing finance companies. Our experts guide you through the plot selection process — ensuring the land has clear title, proper approvals, is within municipal limits, and qualifies for bank financing. We also help you plan a combined plot + construction loan strategy to build your dream home with the most cost-effective financing structure.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.75%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹1 Crore</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">70%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Financing (LTV)</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Plot Loan Interest Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>8.75% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.40%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Ltd</td>
                <td>9.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>9.10% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.00%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bank of Baroda</td>
                <td>8.85% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>PNB Housing</td>
                <td>9.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.00%</td>
                <td>12 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Indian citizen aged between 21 and 60 years (65 for self-employed)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Plot should be within municipal/corporation limits or approved layout</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Clear and marketable title with no legal disputes or encumbrances</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum monthly income of ₹30,000 for salaried applicants</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 720 or above for competitive interest rates</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Construction must begin within 3-5 years of plot purchase (lender-specific)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get a Plot Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Select Your Plot</h4>
              <p>Choose a plot in an approved layout or within municipal limits. Verify the title, encumbrance, and land use classification before finalizing.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Check Financing</h4>
              <p>Enter plot details — location, area, cost, and seller information — to check eligibility and compare offers from 25+ lenders on TrueCred.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Submit Documents</h4>
              <p>Provide plot sale agreement, title documents, land revenue records, and your income proof for the bank's legal and technical verification.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Purchase Your Plot</h4>
              <p>Once approved, the loan amount is disbursed directly to the seller's account. Register the property and start planning your construction.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Plot sale agreement or allotment letter from developer/authority</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Title deed chain — original and all previous ownership transfers</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Encumbrance certificate for the last 15-30 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Land revenue records — Patta, Chitta, Adangal (varies by state)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Approved layout plan and NA (Non-Agricultural) conversion order</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income proof — salary slips, ITR, and bank statements for last 6-12 months</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Apply for Plot Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="7500000">₹75,00,000</option>
                  <option value="10000000">₹1,00,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about plot loans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How is a plot loan different from a home loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              A plot loan finances land purchase only, while a home loan finances the purchase of a constructed property (flat/house). Key differences: plot loan LTV is 70% (vs 80% for home loans), interest rates are typically 0.25-0.50% higher, tenure may be shorter, and construction must begin within a specified period. Tax benefits under Section 80C are available for principal, but Section 24(b) interest deduction applies only after construction is complete.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get tax benefits on a plot loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Tax benefits on plot loans are limited. Principal repayment qualifies under Section 80C (up to ₹1.5 lakh), but the interest deduction under Section 24(b) is available only after construction of the house is completed on the plot. Until then, you can accumulate the interest paid and claim it in 5 equal installments starting from the year construction is completed, subject to the ₹2 lakh annual limit.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What type of plots are eligible for bank financing?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Banks finance plots that are: within municipal/corporation limits or approved township/layout, have clear and marketable title, have been converted to residential/commercial use (NA order for agricultural land), are free from encumbrances and litigation, and comply with local building regulations. Agricultural land, forest land, government land, and land under acquisition are generally not eligible for plot loans.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get both plot loan and construction loan from the same bank?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, most banks offer a combined plot + construction loan (also called composite loan). This is often the best approach as you get a single loan account with one interest rate, one EMI, and simplified documentation. The loan is disbursed in stages — first for plot purchase and then in tranches as construction progresses. Combined loans may also qualify for better interest rates.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the maximum plot loan amount I can get?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              The maximum plot loan depends on the plot value, your income, and the bank's policy. Most banks finance up to 70% of the registered plot value or the bank's own valuation, whichever is lower. The remaining 30% must be your own contribution. Loan amounts range from ₹5 lakhs to ₹1 crore for standard plot loans. For premium plots, some banks may consider higher amounts on a case-by-case basis.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Buy Your Dream Plot with Easy Financing</h3>
          <p>Up to 70% financing on plot purchase at rates from 8.75% p.a. Compare offers from 25+ lenders.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
